#Text=The New York Knicks ( 17 - 64 ) defeated the Atlanta Hawks ( 60 - 21 ) 112 - 108 on Monday at Philips Arena in Atlanta .
#Text=While the Knicks have already been eliminated from the playoffs , this game did carry some weight in regards to their 2015 NBA Draft lottery odds .
#Text=The Timberwolves now have taken over as the worst record in the league , so they 'll likely end up with the highest odds come draft day in June for that number one overall pick .
#Text=The Hawks , on the other hand , were n't affected much by the loss , as they 've already locked up the number one overall seed for the playoffs in the Eastern Conference .
#Text=It still has n't been determined who they 'll play yet , but it should be either the Boston Celtics , Indiana Pacers , Brooklyn Nets or Miami Heat .

#Text=The Knicks were the superior shooters in this game , going 56 percent from the field and 52 percent from the three - point line , while the Hawks finished at 44 percent from the floor and just 34 percent from deep .
#Text=The Knicks turned the ball over 18 times compared to just eight from the Hawks , but they were able to overcome the disparity with their strong shooting .
#Text=Langston Galloway had an extremely impressive performance .
#Text=He went 10 - for - 12 from the field and a perfect 6 - for - 6 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 26 points , while adding five rebounds and six assists as well .

#Text=It was a complete turn around from Saturday 's game against the Magic where he shot just 25 percent ( 4 - 16 FG ) from the field , so the Knicks were happy to see the guard play so well with the season coming to an end .
#Text=Tim Hardaway Jr. also had a very strong showing , finishing with 23 points ( 9 - 17 FG , 3 - 9 3Pt , 2 - 3 FT ) and five assists over 36 minutes .
#Text=It was just the seventh time this season that he 's reached the 20 - point mark , as he 's averaging just 11 points on the season .
#Text=Jason Smith had a big game with 20 points ( 7 - 13 FG , 1 - 2 3Pt , 5 - 5 FT ) , nine rebounds and five assists over 36 minutes as well .
#Text=The Hawks ' backcourt duo of Jeff Teague and Kyle Korver did their best to pull out this win for the Hawks .
#Text=Teague finished with 19 points ( 7 - 17 FG , 1 - 2 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) , nine assists and two steals , while Korver posted 19 points ( 4 - 10 FG , 4 - 9 3Pt , 7 - 7 FT ) and five rebounds .
#Text=Korver has been hitting three - pointers at a very high rate as the season has been winding down .
#Text=He 's made at least three three - pointers in six of his last seven games , which bodes well for the Hawks as the playoffs begin Saturday .
#Text=With Paul Millsap getting the night off in hopes of having his shoulder return closer to 100 percent , both Al Horford and DeMarre Carroll put up some points in the frontcourt .
#Text=Carroll finished with 16 points ( 5 - 11 FG , 2 - 6 3Pt , 4 - 6 FT ) and four rebounds over 33 minutes , while Horford added 18 points ( 9 - 17 FG ) and six rebounds over 33 minutes .
#Text=While the Hawks ' starters all played well , they just happened to run into the Knicks at the wrong time , as the Knicks played one of their best offensive games of the season .
#Text=The Knicks ' final game of the season will be at home against the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday , while the Hawks will travel to Chicago to play the Bulls on Wednesday .
